The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Good Morning
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       Good Morning
      Hello It's Friday , April 18 , 2008                      
	Fight the blaze    Exhibition of fire-fighting and blaze protection equipment at Academy of Fine Arts, 2pm to 8pm.    Workshop and fire-fighting demonstration at Future Foundation School, Regent Park, 11am to 1pm.    
	Stamp    Stamp release on Indian cinema by film-maker Sandip Ray, followed by a screening of Baksho Rahoshyo, at Outram Club, 7pm.    
	Books    Storylines and Songscapes  reading of Tagores short stories translated in English  at GD Birla Sabhagar, 6.30pm.    Launch of Derozio, Poet of India, The Definitive Edition at Oxford Bookstore, 6.30pm.    
	On stage    Abartan at Star Theatre, 6pm.    The Zoo Story at Padatik, 7pm.    
	Lecture     Lecture on Is Calcuttas Heritage in Peril? by Soumitra Das at Jibanananda Sabhaghar, 6pm.    
	Seminar    Inauguration of national symposium on environment and water at Dr Triguna Sen Auditorium, JU, 10am.    
	Music    Programme on Wes Montgomery at Calcutta School of Music, 7pm.    
	Art watch    Calcutta: Chitpur Road and Neighbourhoods, an exhibition, at CIMA Gallery, 2pm to 7pm.                                                                                                                                                                 
